cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the problem of computing the genus of a graph, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents a polynomial-time algorithm for approximating the genus of a graph. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with graph theory and topology. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with the complexity of approximating the Euler genus of a graph. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the NP-hardness of the problem and the approximability of the Euler genus.
